                Personal protection. 
            </div>
            <div class="container col-md-7 safety-panel" id="sfty-acc1">
                   <p> We should always wear a lab coat, nitrile gloves and masks in order to avoid contact with dropplets, aerosols and other contaminants resulting from experiments. We should also wear long pants that cover the ankles, close-toed shoes and long hair (chin-length or longer) should be tied back. 
                    </p>
